WEBVTT

00:46.916 --> 00:48.916
[slow, intriguing
music playing]

01:01.333 --> 01:03.166
[yoga instructor]
Take a deep breath in.

01:04.375 --> 01:06.375
[Davis inhales]

01:16.125 --> 01:17.958
[yoga instructor] And exhale.

01:19.583 --> 01:21.583
[Davis exhales]

01:26.208 --> 01:27.416
[yoga instructor] Inhale...

01:28.333 --> 01:30.333
[Davis inhales]

01:37.250 --> 01:38.833
[yoga instructor] And exhale.

01:40.791 --> 01:41.875
[Davis exhales]

01:49.291 --> 01:52.041
[yoga instructor]
Notice the beat of your heart.

01:55.875 --> 01:58.083
The rhythm of life.

02:04.541 --> 02:05.541
[scrubbing continues]

02:06.916 --> 02:09.250
You hold the power to create

02:09.416 --> 02:12.041
all that you desire
out of nothing.

02:23.583 --> 02:24.750
You okay?

02:25.750 --> 02:26.750
Yeah.

02:29.416 --> 02:30.833
[yoga instructor]
What do you see?

02:34.958 --> 02:36.208
What do you feel?

02:47.083 --> 02:49.916
Remember that there is great
power within you.

02:50.083 --> 02:50.958
[shutter and chain creaking]

02:54.375 --> 02:58.041
And that power will guide you
on your journey.

02:59.500 --> 03:01.125
Let me see the gun.

03:04.958 --> 03:06.166
Is it loaded?

03:09.041 --> 03:10.083
I suggest you load it.

03:10.250 --> 03:11.250
[gun magazine clicks]

03:20.458 --> 03:23.375
[yoga instructor] Today is a
beautiful day of opportunity.

03:28.791 --> 03:31.458
I am exactly
where I need to be.

03:31.625 --> 03:32.625
[sighs]

03:38.041 --> 03:39.208
[alarm ringing]

03:40.583 --> 03:42.916
[yoga instructor] I open
myself to the universe

03:43.083 --> 03:46.333
and trust
in the unfolding of my life.

03:50.791 --> 03:51.666
[sighs softly]

03:58.333 --> 04:00.375
[yoga instructor] This day
will bring you peace

04:01.500 --> 04:04.000
and an opportunity
for success.

04:08.000 --> 04:09.416
[AI voice] Track your buddy.

04:10.791 --> 04:13.375
[yoga instructor]
Feel this moment.

04:13.541 --> 04:15.125
[engine starts]

04:19.166 --> 04:20.375
[tires screech]

04:20.541 --> 04:22.957
Have a beautiful
rest of your day.

04:30.166 --> 04:31.916
[AI voice] You have
found your buddy.

04:34.291 --> 04:35.250
[exhales softly]

04:57.582 --> 04:59.582
[suspenseful music playing]

05:13.166 --> 05:14.250
[exhales deeply]

05:26.791 --> 05:29.207
Don't say anything
unless you have to. Okay?

05:36.000 --> 05:38.666
[car beeping]

05:38.832 --> 05:39.791
[beeping stops]

05:46.875 --> 05:47.875
[clicking]

05:53.541 --> 05:54.541
[bell buzzing]

05:59.832 --> 06:00.875
[speaking Farsi] Are you good?

06:00.958 --> 06:01.958
[Ben speaking Farsi]
Everything is good.

06:02.041 --> 06:03.041
Who is this?

06:03.166 --> 06:04.583
[in English]
This is my cousin.

06:04.750 --> 06:05.916
[Sammy speaking Farsi]
Wasn't Leo your cousin?

06:06.083 --> 06:07.708
[in English] No,
this is my other cousin.

06:07.875 --> 06:09.083
Have you done this before?

06:09.500 --> 06:11.000
Sat in a car for two hours?
Yeah.

06:35.916 --> 06:36.875
[Sammy] Okay?

06:37.041 --> 06:38.207
[Sammy speaking Farsi]
Put them in the case.

06:39.166 --> 06:41.666
Come round the back,
I want to have a word.

06:42.125 --> 06:44.457
[in English]
Ali, not you, stay here.

06:45.832 --> 06:47.625
Just put the watches
in the briefcase, okay?

07:06.291 --> 07:07.291
[exhales deeply]

07:18.500 --> 07:19.582
[Masoud] What the...

07:20.541 --> 07:21.875
[suspenseful music continuing]

07:23.541 --> 07:24.791
Hey, what's the problem?

07:24.957 --> 07:27.082
[breathing heavily]

07:44.916 --> 07:46.375
[Davis] Hands on your head.

07:46.541 --> 07:47.957
You're carrying a gun?

07:48.957 --> 07:50.041
In the car.

07:52.625 --> 07:53.707
-[Davis] All right, get in.
-What?

07:54.416 --> 07:56.000
[Davis] Get in the trunk,
Masoud.

07:57.582 --> 07:58.750
Where's your phone?

07:59.375 --> 08:01.041
-In the car.
-[Davis] What's the PIN?

08:02.583 --> 08:03.791
1324.

08:03.958 --> 08:04.875
[Davis] There's
water in the trunk.

08:05.041 --> 08:07.041
-[thuds]
-[panting]

08:19.125 --> 08:20.125
[exhales sharply]

08:23.000 --> 08:24.457
[Sammy speaking Farsi]
Today is different.

08:25.582 --> 08:27.582
This isn't your usual run.

08:29.166 --> 08:31.791
You're going to transport
two sets of diamonds.

08:34.207 --> 08:35.125
Come closer.

08:38.125 --> 08:40.875
[in English] Six diamonds.
Eight carats each.

08:41.915 --> 08:43.790
[in Farsi] Total value,
3 million dollars.

08:44.333 --> 08:45.625
What about the ones
in the briefcase?

08:46.000 --> 08:47.290
They're fake.

08:47.540 --> 08:48.708
-[in English] Fake?
-Get up.

08:49.500 --> 08:51.625
[speaking Farsi] You need
to tie this to your leg.

08:53.875 --> 08:55.915
And don't tell your cousin.

09:07.750 --> 09:08.750
[phone dings]

09:12.833 --> 09:13.750
Walk.

09:14.708 --> 09:15.583
Yeah it's fine.

09:15.666 --> 09:16.916
-[Sammy] Mmm-hmm.
-Mmm.

09:19.875 --> 09:21.708
See that car
parked across the street?

09:22.250 --> 09:24.666
He's gonna follow you
to Houghtons.

09:24.833 --> 09:26.250
-[in English] Just for safety.
-Okay.

09:26.416 --> 09:27.833
May I see your weapon?

09:31.875 --> 09:33.290
What is this?

09:33.458 --> 09:35.375
-It was my dad's gun.
-Oh, really?

09:35.540 --> 09:38.040
Who was your dad? John Wayne?

09:40.000 --> 09:41.165
Take this.

09:41.333 --> 09:43.540
You bring it straight back.
No stopping.

09:43.708 --> 09:44.915
What did I say?

09:45.790 --> 09:47.040
No stopping.

09:49.625 --> 09:51.125
[suspenseful music continuing]

09:52.415 --> 09:53.415
[indistinct chatter]

10:03.500 --> 10:05.541
[Ali] Guy's
fucking disrespectful.

10:22.125 --> 10:24.041
[Angie] Hey, have you
seen my keys? I'm late.

10:24.208 --> 10:25.750
Hey, can I get
a little privacy?

10:25.916 --> 10:27.416
[Angie] If you're gonna take
a dump, then lock the door.

10:27.583 --> 10:28.750
I'm peeing.

10:28.916 --> 10:30.041
[Angie] You pee
sitting down now?

10:30.208 --> 10:31.541
Best three minutes of my day.

10:31.708 --> 10:33.250
[Angie] Jesus, that's sexy.

10:36.500 --> 10:38.040
[radio host]
Back to the 405...

10:38.208 --> 10:40.165
The 101 westbound
is clear now...

10:40.333 --> 10:42.833
between Echo Park Avenue
and Thousand Oaks.

10:43.000 --> 10:44.583
Not too bad through downtown,
but...

11:26.083 --> 11:27.625
[breathing heavily]

11:33.583 --> 11:34.833
[Ali] What the fuck?

11:43.665 --> 11:45.000
It's your fucking house.

11:47.625 --> 11:49.333
[Davis] Ben, as you can see,
my partner's

11:49.500 --> 11:51.083
parked across the street
from your home.

11:51.875 --> 11:53.333
It's just an insurance policy

11:54.040 --> 11:55.333
same as the jewels
you're carrying,

11:55.500 --> 11:57.500
also covered by insurance.

11:57.665 --> 12:00.250
So let's not do
anything stupid. Understand?

12:01.333 --> 12:03.541
When I say, "go,"
slowly remove your gun,

12:03.708 --> 12:06.375
both your phones,
and throw them into my car.

12:06.541 --> 12:07.541
Clear?

12:08.625 --> 12:09.625
Go.

12:15.916 --> 12:16.958
Slowly.

12:19.166 --> 12:20.833
Stay there. Do not move.

12:23.666 --> 12:24.666
Ben, get out.

12:25.833 --> 12:27.333
Kneel down back of the car.

12:28.666 --> 12:29.875
Eyes forward.

12:30.041 --> 12:31.041
Personally, I wouldn't die

12:31.208 --> 12:32.083
for an insurance company.

12:32.250 --> 12:33.290
Just take it and go.

12:33.458 --> 12:34.833
[Davis] No, Ben, I want
the real diamonds

12:35.000 --> 12:36.125
in the papers. Now.

12:37.000 --> 12:38.000
I don't know
what you're talking about.

12:38.915 --> 12:40.790
I wanna get you home
to Soraya, Ben.

12:40.958 --> 12:42.290
Help me do that.

12:42.458 --> 12:43.333
[breathes shakily]

12:43.833 --> 12:45.583
Where are they?

12:46.875 --> 12:47.875
[exhales deeply]

12:48.415 --> 12:50.208
-My ankle.
-[Davis] Which one?

12:50.290 --> 12:51.125
[Ben] Left.

12:51.208 --> 12:52.125
[Davis] All right,
slowly remove them.

12:56.583 --> 12:57.665
Come on, Ben.

13:04.750 --> 13:05.916
-Get out.
-[Masoud grunts]

13:07.166 --> 13:08.708
Let's go. Fuckin' move.

13:09.166 --> 13:10.208
Kneel down.

13:17.791 --> 13:20.375
Here. I'm betting you didn't
back up your photos.

13:23.458 --> 13:24.833
[Davis breathing heavily]

13:29.375 --> 13:30.375
[gunshot]

13:33.708 --> 13:34.833
-[Davis grunts]
-[car alarm beeping]

13:35.000 --> 13:36.125
[Davis breathing heavily]

13:38.290 --> 13:39.790
[Davis grunts]

13:39.875 --> 13:42.083
-[engine revving]
-[tires screeching]

13:45.040 --> 13:47.415
[panting, sniffling]

13:51.708 --> 13:52.750
[grunting, panting]

13:54.375 --> 13:55.583
-[grunts]
-[tires screeching]

13:57.040 --> 13:58.333
[breathing heavily]

14:07.416 --> 14:08.375
[car honks]

14:11.250 --> 14:12.875
[tires screeching]

14:13.416 --> 14:14.583
[car honking]

14:29.791 --> 14:31.333
-[metal clangs]
-[Davis] Fuck!

14:33.208 --> 14:34.540
[tires screeching]

14:35.165 --> 14:36.040
[grunts]

14:40.500 --> 14:42.415
[tires screeching]

14:45.458 --> 14:47.458
[breathing heavily]

14:58.208 --> 14:59.208
[engine stops]

15:00.041 --> 15:01.541
[breath trembling]

15:04.875 --> 15:06.875
[siren blaring in distance]

15:15.333 --> 15:17.000
[breathing heavily]

15:27.875 --> 15:29.083
[swallows, grunts]

15:30.208 --> 15:32.208
[intriguing music playing]

15:53.083 --> 15:54.083
[car trunk thuds]

15:55.540 --> 15:56.540
[engine starting, revving]

16:01.541 --> 16:03.916
-[engine roars]
-[tires screech]

16:15.625 --> 16:18.083
[Sharon] Wow.
Well, you have a very, uh,

16:18.250 --> 16:20.541
-unique eye.
-[Monroe chuckles]

16:20.708 --> 16:22.666
[Sharon] And your beautiful
home here is a real tribute

16:22.833 --> 16:24.583
to all of your achievements.

16:24.750 --> 16:26.208
What we offer you

16:26.375 --> 16:28.041
is the highest level
of protection

16:28.125 --> 16:29.125
for all of these things

16:29.250 --> 16:31.291
-that you care so much about.
-Okay. Protection?

16:31.458 --> 16:32.458
Come here.

16:33.708 --> 16:35.040
What does this look like?

16:36.208 --> 16:38.750
-Uh, a thermostat?
-Fingerprint activation.

16:38.915 --> 16:41.208
All me and my daughter
have to do is touch it.

16:41.375 --> 16:43.708
-Boom. Opens in a heartbeat.
-Oh.

16:43.875 --> 16:45.708
-Okay, never seen that before.
-Panic safe.

16:46.165 --> 16:47.583
One in every single room.

16:48.290 --> 16:49.915
Well, that's not gonna lower
your insurance premiums...

16:50.083 --> 16:51.915
but I'm certain
it must make you feel better.

16:52.083 --> 16:54.208
It fucking well does.

16:54.375 --> 16:55.833
I had two buddies last year,

16:56.250 --> 16:59.040
had home invaders
while they were in bed.

16:59.208 --> 17:00.375
-Really?
-You ever shoot one?

17:00.541 --> 17:01.541
A home invader?

17:01.708 --> 17:02.958
No, a Glock.

17:04.250 --> 17:06.500
No. Well, that's not exactly
in my line of work.

17:07.000 --> 17:08.083
You're gonna like it.

17:08.250 --> 17:09.750
-No, no, no. No.
-No, it's gonna be good.

17:09.915 --> 17:11.665
Here we go. You ready?

17:11.833 --> 17:12.708
[sighs]

17:12.875 --> 17:14.040
[Monroe] Hey, Ramon?

17:15.375 --> 17:16.875
Could you please move?

17:17.333 --> 17:18.333
Gracias.

17:18.458 --> 17:19.540
I'm probably gonna hit him,
you know.

17:19.708 --> 17:20.833
No, no, no.
You're not gonna hit him.

17:21.000 --> 17:22.500
He gets out of the way
all the time.

17:22.665 --> 17:23.708
All right, I'll take that,

17:24.290 --> 17:25.500
and you take this.

17:26.540 --> 17:27.915
And if you hit
one of those bottles...

17:28.083 --> 17:30.416
I'll sign your policy
right now.

17:30.583 --> 17:31.583
[Sharon breathes deeply]

17:32.125 --> 17:33.125
Okay. [sighs]

17:33.291 --> 17:35.458
Here you go. Just go ahead
and point... There you go.

17:36.041 --> 17:37.000
All you do is relax,

17:37.166 --> 17:38.958
and you just squeeze
when you're ready, okay?

17:41.083 --> 17:42.916
-[gunshot]
-Oh! Oh, God.

17:43.083 --> 17:45.708
[laughs] Well,
you didn't hit Ramon.

17:45.875 --> 17:47.958
That's good. That's good news.
There you go.

17:49.166 --> 17:51.166
All right, next up.

17:51.333 --> 17:53.208
This needs
to be on the policy,

17:53.375 --> 17:55.583
as it is definitely
appreciated

17:55.750 --> 17:56.916
since I bought it.

17:57.958 --> 18:00.333
I've only seen that
inside a museum.

18:00.500 --> 18:03.375
[Monroe] Cost me
6.2 million dollars.

18:03.541 --> 18:05.041
But we both know

18:05.208 --> 18:06.458
contemporary Black art

18:06.625 --> 18:08.041
is only going
in one direction.

18:08.416 --> 18:09.416
Right?

18:10.208 --> 18:12.625
Uh, listen, we got
a lot of stuff to go through.

18:12.791 --> 18:15.625
We got a lot
of high-tech stuff in here.

18:15.791 --> 18:16.833
[Sharon] What
makes us different,

18:17.208 --> 18:19.666
is that we also
protect your privacy.

18:20.208 --> 18:23.916
Um, for example,
we also have cyber liability.

18:24.083 --> 18:25.541
Do you remember
the admission scandal

18:25.625 --> 18:26.583
of a few years back?

18:26.750 --> 18:28.125
-I do, yeah.
-[Sharon] Yeah, well,

18:28.291 --> 18:29.625
none of our clients
were named in that.

18:30.208 --> 18:32.083
And... hello.

18:32.250 --> 18:34.583
We also will cover
your daughter's possessions

18:34.750 --> 18:36.416
as she goes off to college.

18:37.416 --> 18:39.041
That's my fiancée...

18:39.208 --> 18:40.375
Adrienne.

18:42.000 --> 18:43.583
[Sharon] Lovely to meet you,
Adrienne.

18:43.750 --> 18:44.833
We were just about to talk

18:45.000 --> 18:47.500
about, uh, your coverage
for your wedding.

18:47.666 --> 18:50.333
Sounds like
it's a beautiful venue.

18:50.916 --> 18:51.791
[exhales deeply]

18:53.791 --> 18:55.958
Are you gonna be long...
[sarcastically] "Daddy"?

18:56.125 --> 18:57.750
[Monroe] No,
we're totally done here.

18:59.000 --> 18:59.916
[Sharon sighs]

19:00.083 --> 19:01.041
[radio host]
That's where gridlock,

19:01.208 --> 19:02.208
-Getty Center Drive...
-Sharon.

19:02.375 --> 19:03.416
[radio host] ...has the two
right lanes blocked

19:03.500 --> 19:04.666
with the backup
starting at the 101.

19:04.833 --> 19:06.916
Southbound Sepulveda will work
for you, getting from

19:07.000 --> 19:08.583
-West LA to the airport.
-[Sharon sighs]

19:08.666 --> 19:10.083
[rock song playing over radio]

19:26.291 --> 19:27.875
[radio announcer] ...infused
with organic coconut,

19:28.041 --> 19:29.000
aloe vera...

19:31.875 --> 19:34.208
[Lou] Well, well, well,
right next to the 101.

19:34.375 --> 19:36.458
Oh, don't fucking
start on that shit, Lou.

19:37.833 --> 19:40.500
Jesus Christ, you ever gonna
swap out that shit bucket?

19:41.250 --> 19:42.750
There's nothing wrong
with that shit bucket.

19:42.916 --> 19:44.541
It's maturing
like a fine wine.

19:44.708 --> 19:45.708
-Is it?
-Yeah.

19:45.875 --> 19:46.708
[Tillman scoffs]

19:46.791 --> 19:48.166
It's depressing,
is what it is, man.

19:48.333 --> 19:49.458
I just, I can't understand

19:49.625 --> 19:50.916
why you wanna
look so fucking poor.

19:51.083 --> 19:53.125
[scoffs] That ain't
what poor looks like.

19:53.291 --> 19:54.833
What do you care so much for?

19:55.000 --> 19:56.041
Because I gotta be seen

19:56.208 --> 19:58.458
riding in it with you,
Detective Buddha.

19:58.625 --> 20:00.083
[Lou] Yeah.

20:00.250 --> 20:01.541
What do we got here?

20:01.708 --> 20:03.583
[Tillman] Round the back.
Courier got hit...

20:03.750 --> 20:05.833
carrying three mil worth
of stones from downtown.

20:06.250 --> 20:07.666
He just left these behind,
Ben?

20:08.541 --> 20:10.875
What, he somehow knew
these were fakes or...

20:11.375 --> 20:12.458
[Ben] I don't know.

20:13.208 --> 20:14.375
[Tillman] We don't know.

20:15.291 --> 20:17.041
Okay. What else
can you tell us, Ben?

20:18.083 --> 20:19.875
He knew my wife's name.

20:20.041 --> 20:21.875
[suspenseful music playing]

20:23.458 --> 20:25.500
And how would he know that?

20:25.666 --> 20:27.166
How the fuck
should I know, huh?

20:27.333 --> 20:28.750
Why are you asking me
all this shit?

20:28.916 --> 20:29.791
[chuckles] Easy.

20:29.875 --> 20:31.875
Because, Ben,
the one day you're carrying...

20:32.041 --> 20:34.125
nearly three mil in stones
is the day you get hit.

20:34.291 --> 20:35.750
I mean, that's a little bit
of a coincidence, no?

20:35.916 --> 20:37.083
Well, I didn't give him
any information

20:37.250 --> 20:38.125
if that's what
you're asking, okay?

20:38.291 --> 20:39.333
-[Tillman] I didn't say...
-You know what?

20:39.416 --> 20:40.375
This is victim blaming,
what you're doing.

20:40.458 --> 20:41.666
-Yes.
-[Tillman] I'm victim blaming.

20:41.833 --> 20:43.541
-Is that what I'm doing?
-Did he take your phones?

20:43.708 --> 20:46.291
Yeah, he did,
but he gave them back.

20:48.083 --> 20:49.916
Your cousin says
you shot at him.

20:50.666 --> 20:52.333
The gun fucking misfired.

20:52.666 --> 20:53.666
He had a gun?

20:55.000 --> 20:57.291
-Yeah.
-Why didn't he shoot you?

20:59.583 --> 21:01.041
You'll have to ask him.

21:01.208 --> 21:02.666
-Told you don't start on that.
-Start on what?

21:02.833 --> 21:05.583
-That lone ranger shit.
-It's his M.O., man.

21:05.750 --> 21:06.625
What do you mean, "his M.O.?"

21:06.791 --> 21:07.875
The M.O. of not leaving
clues behind?

21:08.041 --> 21:10.291
He knows exactly what
they're transporting, when.

21:10.458 --> 21:12.541
He cuts the camera line
in advance.

21:12.708 --> 21:13.708
There's no violence.

21:13.875 --> 21:14.791
He's in and out in seconds,

21:14.958 --> 21:16.208
-or he disappears.
-Okay.

21:16.375 --> 21:17.583
We're right next to the 101.

21:17.750 --> 21:19.000
Come on, he's got rules.

21:19.166 --> 21:21.583
-Rules? He's got rules?
-Yeah, and he sticks to 'em.

21:21.750 --> 21:22.666
Yeah, this gonna
be another one

21:22.833 --> 21:23.666
we eat shit for,
isn't it, Lou?

21:23.833 --> 21:24.750
No one's eating shit.

21:27.208 --> 21:29.291
-[Tillman sighs]
-What's goin' on with you?

21:32.000 --> 21:33.041
[Tillman scoffs]

21:33.208 --> 21:34.666
The lieutenant says...

21:36.000 --> 21:37.791
I should look
into a change of partner.

21:38.791 --> 21:41.208
Says if I stick with you,
I'll end up languishing.

21:41.791 --> 21:43.041
[Lou] Did he?

21:43.208 --> 21:44.208
[Tillman] Yep.

21:45.250 --> 21:46.541
Well, what'd you say?

21:47.000 --> 21:48.583
I told him
I didn't want to do that.

21:51.666 --> 21:52.500
Thanks.

21:52.583 --> 21:54.916
But this lone wolf
obsession of yours,

21:55.083 --> 21:56.583
it ain't winning us
any friends.

21:56.750 --> 21:58.541
It's the same guy,
and I know it.

21:58.708 --> 21:59.916
Well, you better
be fucking right, Lou.

22:00.083 --> 22:01.125
[engine starts]

22:01.291 --> 22:03.208
'Cause I need to step up, man,
and soon.

22:03.375 --> 22:05.375
[suspenseful music playing]

22:14.500 --> 22:15.333
[sighs]

22:17.625 --> 22:18.625
[Davis exhales deeply]

22:20.166 --> 22:22.375
[paper rustling]

22:53.750 --> 22:55.750
[breathing heavily]

23:05.916 --> 23:06.916
[breath trembles]

23:11.791 --> 23:12.958
-[Sharon exhales]
-[elevator bell dings]

23:15.000 --> 23:16.375
[woman] Right next to Charles.

23:18.416 --> 23:19.791
[indistinct chatter]

23:19.958 --> 23:21.750
-[telephone rings]
-[man] No, no, no.

23:27.625 --> 23:28.625
[exhales deeply]

23:32.875 --> 23:34.291
[knocking on door]

23:35.083 --> 23:36.916
[Phil] So how'd it go?

23:37.708 --> 23:39.791
Did he show you his weapons?

23:39.958 --> 23:41.666
Not all of them, I hope.
[chuckles]

23:41.833 --> 23:43.166
[Sharon] It went good.

23:43.750 --> 23:44.958
Did you close?

23:45.125 --> 23:46.125
[Sharon] Yeah, basically.

23:46.625 --> 23:50.041
He just, you know, wants to...
look over the quote.

23:51.208 --> 23:52.958
Guy's like a gazillionaire.
He's got time for that?

23:53.125 --> 23:55.000
Hey, I guess
that's how you stay rich.

23:55.333 --> 23:56.583
Well, right.

23:56.750 --> 23:58.333
Well, sure you nailed it.

23:58.875 --> 24:00.250
Uh, Phil?

24:00.333 --> 24:01.333
Yeah.

24:01.416 --> 24:02.625
[Sharon] Any word
on the meeting?

24:03.208 --> 24:04.291
What meeting would that be?

24:04.458 --> 24:05.750
The partners' meeting.

24:05.916 --> 24:07.500
The one
to finalize my partnership.

24:08.375 --> 24:09.458
Yeah, yeah, yeah, um...

24:10.750 --> 24:11.583
Yeah, no, the, uh...

24:11.750 --> 24:13.166
I just gotta get the senior
team around the same table,

24:13.333 --> 24:15.291
but Mark is just back from
Maui, so let me chase it up.

24:15.458 --> 24:17.041
Yeah, but that's what you said
before he left.

24:17.208 --> 24:19.583
Yeah, well, I'm not in charge
of calendars, Sharon, so...

24:19.750 --> 24:21.000
-Well...
-Can we not?

24:21.125 --> 24:21.958
[sighs]

24:24.416 --> 24:25.583
[sizzling]

24:25.666 --> 24:27.083
[indistinct chatter]

24:36.458 --> 24:37.750
[Money] So how'd it go?

24:41.833 --> 24:42.875
Uh...

24:43.041 --> 24:45.083
There was, uh, an incident.

24:46.333 --> 24:47.833
Police?

24:48.833 --> 24:51.708
Nah, just some kid,
you know, it nearly went...

24:54.208 --> 24:55.208
I don't know.

24:59.541 --> 25:00.541
Do you believe in omens?

25:01.041 --> 25:02.333
Fuck omens.

25:02.958 --> 25:05.291
You got shook up, that's all.

25:05.458 --> 25:08.208
This and the next one
in Santa Barbara,

25:08.375 --> 25:10.166
you'll have had a good year.

25:11.666 --> 25:12.750
And you'll have
a good year, too,

25:12.916 --> 25:13.958
and I'm taking all the risk.

25:14.583 --> 25:16.041
You're just selling it.

25:16.208 --> 25:17.958
Something bothering you?

25:18.583 --> 25:20.666
It's just the Santa Barbara
job, you know,

25:20.833 --> 25:22.083
it doesn't feel right.

25:26.875 --> 25:30.166
That's a lot of money
to leave on the table, champ.

25:30.750 --> 25:32.708
I have a buyer waiting.

25:32.875 --> 25:35.208
I know, but it's happening
in the middle of the day.

25:36.000 --> 25:37.500
And we're going straight
in through the front door.

25:37.583 --> 25:38.541
There's no way of knowing

25:38.625 --> 25:40.041
how many people
will be in the car.

25:40.375 --> 25:41.666
Someone could get hurt.

25:41.833 --> 25:44.000
You got
something else in mind?

25:45.375 --> 25:47.166
Yeah, working on something.

25:47.333 --> 25:49.000
[Money] Well, good.

25:49.166 --> 25:52.833
Now look,
go spend some money...

25:53.000 --> 25:55.041
get laid, relax.

25:59.166 --> 26:00.166
[Davis] See you later.

26:03.083 --> 26:03.916
[Money sighs]

26:08.000 --> 26:08.958
[line ringing]

26:09.916 --> 26:10.916
[Ormon] Yeah?

26:11.083 --> 26:13.458
Do you know who this is?

26:13.541 --> 26:15.541
[intriguing music playing]

26:23.208 --> 26:24.166
[door lock clicking]

26:28.958 --> 26:30.125
Jonathan?

26:31.916 --> 26:33.875
What happened to Sarah?

26:34.041 --> 26:36.000
Sarah's not well tonight,
sweetie.

26:36.166 --> 26:37.583
She said she messaged you.

26:41.208 --> 26:42.208
Okay.

26:55.583 --> 26:57.416
[softly] So what
do you like to do?

26:58.083 --> 26:59.041
[Davis smacks lips hesitantly]

26:59.166 --> 27:00.041
Uh, I don't know,

27:00.166 --> 27:02.625
just, uh, normal stuff,
I guess.

27:03.541 --> 27:04.750
[softly] That sounds nice.

27:12.500 --> 27:14.000
[clothes rustling]

27:27.000 --> 27:30.333
Are you an eye contact
or a no eye contact guy?

27:36.916 --> 27:38.166
[exhales deeply]

27:41.625 --> 27:43.208
[alarm chiming]

27:43.375 --> 27:44.833
[yoga instructor]
Good morning.

27:45.000 --> 27:48.833
May this day be a clean slate
for your mind...

27:49.583 --> 27:51.250
for your actions...

27:51.416 --> 27:53.083
for your thoughts.

27:53.250 --> 27:54.583
May this day bring...

27:59.458 --> 28:00.458
[Sharon sighs]

28:03.583 --> 28:04.583
[sighs heavily]

28:19.625 --> 28:22.166
[Mark] Uh, before we begin,
it is my pleasure to introduce

28:22.500 --> 28:24.750
the latest member
of our valuation team,

28:24.916 --> 28:25.875
Madeleine Adcock.

28:26.041 --> 28:28.083
Along with Sharon,
Madeleine's gonna focus

28:28.250 --> 28:29.958
on high net worth residential.

28:30.125 --> 28:32.250
I'm sure we will all
make her feel welcome.

28:32.416 --> 28:33.625
[team clapping]

28:33.791 --> 28:36.208
Hey, guys. Thanks.

28:36.375 --> 28:37.625
Thrilled to be here, guys.

28:38.083 --> 28:39.916
[Mark] Um, okay, new business.

28:40.291 --> 28:41.333
Sharon just valued

28:41.500 --> 28:44.125
one of the wealthiest estates
in all of California

28:44.291 --> 28:45.500
and what is likely to be

28:45.666 --> 28:48.833
the most expensive wedding
we have ever insured.

28:49.625 --> 28:51.750
What's the good word
for Monroe, Sharon?

28:51.916 --> 28:53.500
Uh, it is promising.

28:54.625 --> 28:56.708
[Mark] Okay.
Well, promising is good

28:57.333 --> 28:58.583
but closed is better.

28:58.750 --> 29:00.041
[laughter]

29:00.208 --> 29:02.083
Uh, next up is Phil.
What do you got?

29:02.250 --> 29:04.333
Yeah, something fishy
on the claims side.

29:04.500 --> 29:07.791
Seven-figure claim
from a jeweler, Samir Kassem.

29:07.958 --> 29:09.416
Courier gets robbed
the one day in years if ever

29:09.583 --> 29:11.708
he's transporting three mil
in diamonds. [scoffs]

29:11.875 --> 29:13.000
-[Mark] Yeah.
-Big coincidence, right?

29:13.333 --> 29:15.583
[Mark] Big coincidence.
Sharon, think maybe you could

29:15.750 --> 29:17.500
work your charms with
one of our friends in blue,

29:17.666 --> 29:19.708
get him to polygraph
the vendor?

29:20.625 --> 29:21.750
This week?

29:21.916 --> 29:23.708
I was planning
to follow up with Monroe.

29:23.875 --> 29:25.750
-So...
-It's a seven-figure claim.

29:26.458 --> 29:27.791
[Phil] Okay, how about
we have Madeleine

29:27.958 --> 29:29.166
take over the follow-up
with Monroe?

29:29.333 --> 29:30.916
You know,
fresh face, fresh approach.

29:31.083 --> 29:32.083
[Mark] Good idea, Phil.

29:32.250 --> 29:34.166
[Madeleine] Yeah, I'd be happy
to take it over.

29:34.541 --> 29:35.958
If that's okay with you.

29:36.750 --> 29:37.833
Yeah, sure.

29:38.000 --> 29:40.416
[Mark] Okay, next,
uh, international...

29:40.583 --> 29:42.416
Sammy, you can
see how this looks,

29:42.500 --> 29:43.375
-right?
-No.

29:43.458 --> 29:45.000
No, I don't. No.

29:45.166 --> 29:46.958
Okay, what is this? Hmm?

29:47.125 --> 29:48.208
Fat cop, bad cop?

29:49.208 --> 29:50.041
When do you think

29:50.125 --> 29:50.958
-I started this business?
-[Tillman chuckles]

29:51.125 --> 29:53.541
I opened my store 27 years ago

29:53.708 --> 29:55.291
and I got two other stores.

29:55.458 --> 29:56.708
Why in the world
would I cheat on my own...

29:56.875 --> 29:58.250
[Lou] Okay, let's calm down.

29:58.958 --> 29:59.833
Did you call him...

30:00.000 --> 30:01.083
-[sighs]
-...to tell him when to expect

30:01.250 --> 30:02.458
the courier?

30:02.625 --> 30:04.500
No, I emailed.

30:04.666 --> 30:06.291
[suspenseful music playing]

30:06.958 --> 30:08.500
So now what you gotta
ask yourself is...

30:08.666 --> 30:10.916
"How does he know
whose email to hack?"

30:12.166 --> 30:13.125
And how could he know

30:13.291 --> 30:14.750
who's intending
to transport something

30:14.916 --> 30:16.166
before they transport it?

30:16.333 --> 30:18.416
It's the same
as last time, email,

30:19.083 --> 30:21.833
calendar, Facebook,
WhatsApp, Instagram.

30:22.000 --> 30:23.208
What, no Snapchat? TikTok?

30:23.375 --> 30:24.791
She's too old for that.

30:35.250 --> 30:36.125
[camera clicks]

30:38.541 --> 30:40.541
-[engine revving]
-[vehicles honking]

30:40.625 --> 30:42.625
[rap song playing]

31:13.291 --> 31:14.250
[sighs]

31:15.708 --> 31:16.625
[song stops]

31:16.791 --> 31:17.791
Boo. [chuckles]

31:18.875 --> 31:19.708
[Money clears throat]

31:21.583 --> 31:23.333
[Money] There's a job...

31:23.875 --> 31:25.916
-up in Santa Barbara.
-[Ormon] Mmm-hmm.

31:26.750 --> 31:29.125
My guy has laid it all out

31:29.291 --> 31:31.291
but he's not doing it.

31:31.750 --> 31:32.750
Why ain't he doing it?

31:32.916 --> 31:35.083
He's lost his nerve.

31:36.416 --> 31:37.875
I've seen it before.

31:39.000 --> 31:41.833
He thinks
someone could get hurt.

31:42.000 --> 31:42.916
[Ormon chuckles]

31:43.833 --> 31:44.708
[Ormon] Mmm.

31:44.875 --> 31:45.791
[Ormon inhales deeply]

31:45.958 --> 31:48.333
My dad always said, "You gotta
break a few eggs," so...

31:49.833 --> 31:52.250
Oh, you're not your dad.

31:52.416 --> 31:54.166
God rest his soul.

31:54.333 --> 31:56.041
You might not have the stomach

31:56.208 --> 31:58.458
for some of the things he did.

31:58.833 --> 32:01.250
But if you want
a chance to find out...

32:02.083 --> 32:03.416
this is it.

32:05.875 --> 32:08.166
You think you can handle it?

32:12.000 --> 32:13.000
[indistinct radio chatter]

32:14.625 --> 32:16.250
[suspenseful music continuing]

32:41.208 --> 32:42.708
-[tires screech]
-[car thuds]

32:42.875 --> 32:44.083
-[alarm beeping]
-[mumbling] Oh...

32:45.416 --> 32:46.500
[Maya] Fuck!

32:48.583 --> 32:49.583
Fuck.

32:57.125 --> 32:59.125
Fuck, man,
why'd you stop so suddenly?

32:59.291 --> 33:01.666
I stopped, but there's
nothing sudden about it.

33:01.833 --> 33:02.833
Red light.

33:03.375 --> 33:04.791
-[Maya sighs]
-You okay? You...

33:05.000 --> 33:08.333
No, I'm not okay. I'm late,
and this is my boss's car.

33:08.916 --> 33:11.666
Um... Shit. I just, can I...

33:11.833 --> 33:14.000
I need to get
your insurance information.

33:14.666 --> 33:15.833
Yeah, uh...

33:18.125 --> 33:19.375
Listen, why don't...

33:20.791 --> 33:22.750
Take this and that should
cover the damage.

33:22.916 --> 33:24.333
We don't have to worry about
the whole insurance.

33:24.500 --> 33:26.083
What? You just
have this wad of cash

33:26.250 --> 33:27.958
you wanna pay to not
have the hassle? I don't...

33:28.125 --> 33:30.250
I'm trying to help you out.
You crashed into me.

33:31.541 --> 33:32.416
[sputtering]
I appreciate that,

33:32.500 --> 33:34.583
but I have to go through
the proper channels.

33:34.750 --> 33:36.000
Otherwise I'm gonna get fired.

33:37.125 --> 33:38.250
Let me get a pen.

33:38.416 --> 33:39.625
Yeah, right.

33:40.958 --> 33:44.000
[Maya] Fucking thousands
of dollars in your pocket?

33:49.333 --> 33:50.458
-[sighs]
-[car door closes]

33:52.333 --> 33:53.250
[Maya sighs]

33:56.541 --> 33:57.541
[Maya sighs]

34:00.416 --> 34:01.416
Okay.

34:02.541 --> 34:03.541
Sorry.

34:03.708 --> 34:04.708
[Davis] Um...

34:07.041 --> 34:08.208
[Maya sniffles]

34:14.250 --> 34:16.750
-Here you go.
-Well, okay.

34:17.416 --> 34:19.166
You got, uh, kids?

34:21.333 --> 34:22.916
-What?
-There's a car seat.

34:23.458 --> 34:24.458
Oh, uh...

34:24.625 --> 34:27.250
No. No. God. They're, um...

34:27.416 --> 34:29.291
-It's my boss's car.
-Oh, yeah. Yeah.

34:29.458 --> 34:32.000
She's got a pair of twins.
They're pieces of shit.

34:34.166 --> 34:36.375
Yeah, I don't
have kids either.

34:40.750 --> 34:42.291
-Um...
-Okay.

34:45.375 --> 34:48.208
Um, I guess
someone will be in touch.

34:48.291 --> 34:49.166
I don't know

34:49.250 --> 34:50.708
-how this works, so...
-Great. Yeah, you know...

34:50.875 --> 34:51.875
See you later.

35:01.916 --> 35:02.916
[sighs]

35:12.416 --> 35:15.166
Excuse me. Hey, I guess
you're the insurance lady?

35:15.291 --> 35:16.500
Ah. And I guess

35:16.666 --> 35:18.458
-you're the detective man?
-Yeah.

35:18.625 --> 35:19.791
Sharon Coombs.

35:20.750 --> 35:22.541
-Thanks for meeting with me.
-Sure.

35:23.375 --> 35:25.708
-Want one of these?
-Nah, no, thanks. I'm good.

35:26.083 --> 35:27.083
You don't like smoothies?

35:27.250 --> 35:29.666
I don't even like
to say the word "smoothie."

35:30.208 --> 35:31.041
[Sharon] Mmm.

35:31.208 --> 35:33.666
So you got something for me
on the Kassem case?

35:33.833 --> 35:35.750
Actually, we were hoping
you would consider

35:35.916 --> 35:37.750
polygraphing Kassem
and the courier.

35:37.916 --> 35:39.916
Why, so you could deny
his insurance claim?

35:40.083 --> 35:41.625
He paid his premiums.

35:41.791 --> 35:43.500
What do you wanna do?
You wanna screw him in return?

35:43.666 --> 35:45.125
That's a nice job
you got there, Sharon.

35:45.291 --> 35:46.666
-Yeah? And how's...
-Nice.

35:47.208 --> 35:49.041
...public service
working out for you?

35:50.083 --> 35:51.125
All you hoped it would be?

35:51.958 --> 35:54.125
I mean, you do make
the world a safer place

35:54.291 --> 35:57.833
so, I guess that's
job satisfaction for you, huh?

35:58.000 --> 35:58.833
Least I'm not screwing

35:59.000 --> 35:59.916
the people
I'm paid to protect.

36:00.833 --> 36:02.291
I'm not screwing over anybody.

36:02.875 --> 36:03.750
What we provide

36:03.833 --> 36:06.291
is what people want most
in the world after wealth.

36:06.458 --> 36:08.166
-Wouldn't that be good health?
-Nope.

36:08.333 --> 36:09.541
That's security of wealth.

36:09.708 --> 36:11.916
Ah, damn it. And here
I was brought up to believe

36:12.083 --> 36:13.708
that money
can't buy you happiness.

36:13.875 --> 36:15.791
I'm sorry. You've been misled.

36:16.333 --> 36:18.541
Studies show that happiness
in the over-45s

36:18.708 --> 36:21.541
is overwhelmingly tied
to financial security.

36:21.708 --> 36:24.250
I'm just talking
about a comfortable life

36:24.416 --> 36:26.125
in a nice,
little neighborhood.

36:26.291 --> 36:28.375
Got your piece
of the American pie, Sharon?

36:31.000 --> 36:32.291
I live here by the beach.

36:32.458 --> 36:34.958
Why else would anybody
wanna live in this town?

36:37.708 --> 36:40.416
You know, statistics point
to this being an inside job.

36:40.583 --> 36:42.083
-Statistics?
-Yes.

36:42.458 --> 36:45.208
Every series of human actions
creates a pattern.

36:46.208 --> 36:47.833
Now, I could show you a map

36:48.000 --> 36:50.250
that would predict
where 90% of the people

36:50.416 --> 36:53.125
who develop heart disease
will live in LA

36:53.291 --> 36:54.625
and I can tell you...

36:55.416 --> 36:57.166
it's nowhere around here.

36:57.666 --> 36:58.833
It's science.

36:59.791 --> 37:02.125
-Nice to meet you, Sharon.
-It's nice to meet you, too.

37:02.291 --> 37:03.791
And, you know,
we are well within our rights

37:03.958 --> 37:05.041
to polygraph.

37:05.625 --> 37:07.625
[suspenseful music playing]

37:08.875 --> 37:09.875
[engine idling]

37:30.500 --> 37:33.500
[Lou] Every series
of human actions

37:33.666 --> 37:34.916
creates a pattern.

37:35.083 --> 37:38.875
The area you're looking at
has seen 219 robberies

37:39.041 --> 37:41.041
in the last four years.

37:41.541 --> 37:43.333
Arthur, can you please remove

37:43.500 --> 37:45.375
every robbery under 500K?

37:45.458 --> 37:46.375
[projector beeps]

37:46.458 --> 37:48.125
-Boom.
-[Fellner] Ooh. CSI.

37:48.291 --> 37:49.125
[laughter]

37:49.291 --> 37:50.500
Go ahead. Just here to listen.

37:52.416 --> 37:53.708
Remove every robbery

37:53.875 --> 37:57.041
that doesn't involve
a courier delivery service

37:57.208 --> 37:59.166
-or an armored vehicle.
-[projector beeps]

37:59.666 --> 38:02.250
Now remove every robbery

38:02.416 --> 38:05.458
where there was some type
of violence used in a crime.

38:05.625 --> 38:06.500
[projector beeps]

38:08.750 --> 38:11.750
Lastly, remove every robbery

38:11.916 --> 38:14.250
where there was
some DNA or evidence

38:14.416 --> 38:15.916
left at the scene.

38:16.083 --> 38:17.000
[projector beeps]

38:17.708 --> 38:18.791
Boom.

38:20.166 --> 38:21.375
As smart as our guy is,

38:21.541 --> 38:23.541
he can't help
but form a pattern.

38:23.708 --> 38:24.916
He knows when the jewelers

38:25.083 --> 38:26.250
are moving merchandise
and when...

38:26.416 --> 38:28.500
I believe by hacking
their communications.

38:28.666 --> 38:29.666
He doesn't use violence.

38:29.833 --> 38:31.000
In every single case

38:31.166 --> 38:33.666
he hits along the 101 Freeway.

38:34.958 --> 38:37.458
Last time was south.
I bet the next time is north.

38:42.250 --> 38:43.250
[car door closes]

38:49.083 --> 38:50.541
[suspenseful music playing]

38:52.958 --> 38:54.000
[car honks]

39:00.125 --> 39:01.333
[door release buzzes]

39:01.416 --> 39:02.291
[Ormon] Get the fuck down!

39:02.375 --> 39:03.750
[people gasping]

39:04.208 --> 39:05.750
-[Ormon] Give me the case!
-What?

39:05.916 --> 39:07.458
-[Ormon grunts]
-What the fuck?

39:07.625 --> 39:09.625
[grunting]

39:09.791 --> 39:11.416
-[Ormon] Hey, you, hands up!
-[women gasping]

39:11.583 --> 39:12.750
Get your fucking hands up!

39:12.916 --> 39:13.916
-Hey, come here!
-No.

39:14.083 --> 39:15.125
[Ormon] Come here!

39:15.291 --> 39:16.666
Get on the fucking ground.

39:16.833 --> 39:18.375
Is there anyone in back?

39:19.000 --> 39:19.833
Is there anyone

39:19.916 --> 39:21.208
-in the fucking back?
-No!

39:21.375 --> 39:22.500
There's nobody in the back.

39:22.916 --> 39:24.083
There's nobody there.

39:24.250 --> 39:25.583
[Ormon panting]

39:29.166 --> 39:30.000
[baby cries]

39:30.083 --> 39:31.791
[Ormon] There's no one
in the fucking back, huh?

39:31.958 --> 39:33.041
There's no one
in the fucking back?

39:33.125 --> 39:33.958
[woman exclaims]

39:34.375 --> 39:35.500
[Ormon] Shut up!

39:36.166 --> 39:38.000
-You, where's the key?
-I don't have it.

39:38.166 --> 39:39.250
[Ormon] Where's
the fucking key?

39:39.458 --> 39:41.000
[Grant] It's outside.
It's in the car!

39:41.166 --> 39:42.000
It's in the car outside.

39:42.083 --> 39:42.916
[Ormon] Where's
the fucking key?

39:43.083 --> 39:44.791
-[Grant] It's in the car.
-[Ormon] What fucking car?

39:44.958 --> 39:45.958
[Grant] It's outside.

39:46.375 --> 39:47.375
[Ormon] Fuck!

39:48.500 --> 39:49.833
You think I'm playing games?

39:50.666 --> 39:53.416
Give me... the fucking... key!

39:53.583 --> 39:55.750
-Or I fucking kill you!
-Okay, it's on my neck!

39:55.916 --> 39:57.125
I'll give it to you.
I'll give it to you.

39:57.291 --> 39:58.500
[Ormon] Now! Fuckin' over it!

39:58.666 --> 39:59.916
-[Grant] Take it!
-[Ormon] Come on!

40:00.083 --> 40:01.125
[Grant] Just, it's...
You're fuckin'...

40:01.250 --> 40:02.375
[baby continues crying]

40:02.916 --> 40:04.666
[Ormon] Someone
shut the baby up.

40:05.583 --> 40:06.583
What?

40:09.041 --> 40:10.041
[grumbles]

40:10.291 --> 40:12.166
You, open
the fucking cabinets!

40:12.333 --> 40:14.208
What the fuck? What is the...

40:14.791 --> 40:15.791
-Unlock it!
-I don't work here!

40:15.958 --> 40:17.208
I don't work here!
I don't work here! No!

40:17.375 --> 40:18.833
-[man] Doesn't work here.
-I don't work here!

40:19.000 --> 40:20.375
-[Ormon] Sit the fuck down!
-[woman exclaims]

40:21.250 --> 40:24.250
[Ormon] Okay, go around,
unlock it. Now!

40:24.416 --> 40:26.000
Don't you fucking look at me.

40:26.166 --> 40:27.541
-Open the... Open it.
-It's open.

40:27.708 --> 40:29.083
Put it in the bag.

40:29.250 --> 40:31.000
Hurry up! Come on!

40:32.166 --> 40:33.166
Come on.

40:34.541 --> 40:35.458
Come on!

40:35.625 --> 40:36.833
Come back around!

40:37.458 --> 40:39.333
Get the fuck
back on the ground!

40:39.500 --> 40:40.916
Hurry the fuck up!

40:42.041 --> 40:43.083
You, come here!

40:43.250 --> 40:44.958
Lay on him! Lay on him!

40:45.458 --> 40:46.875
Get the fuck on top.

40:48.500 --> 40:49.500
Stay.

40:52.458 --> 40:53.958
[grunts] Fuck.

40:54.125 --> 40:55.291
Where's the fucking
door release?

40:55.458 --> 40:56.708
-It's next to the till!
-[Ormon] What?

40:56.875 --> 40:57.916
[baby continues crying]

40:58.083 --> 40:59.000
[Ormon groans]

40:59.083 --> 41:00.000
[woman sobbing]

41:00.083 --> 41:02.041
[Ormon] It's where?
Where? Where the fuck?

41:02.208 --> 41:03.208
[door release buzzes]

41:04.875 --> 41:06.208
[Ormon] It's okay, shut up.

41:09.750 --> 41:11.708
-[door rattling]
-Fuck! Fuck!

41:12.583 --> 41:13.750
Fucking... Fucking...

41:14.041 --> 41:16.291
You, get the door! Now!

41:16.666 --> 41:17.625
-[gunshot]
-[all scream]

41:18.208 --> 41:19.583
[Ormon] Open the fucking door!

41:19.750 --> 41:22.250
Okay, okay, okay.

41:22.416 --> 41:23.750
Easy. Easy.

41:23.916 --> 41:24.791
[alarm ringing]

41:25.833 --> 41:27.916
-[door release buzzing]
-[Ormon] Remember...

41:28.083 --> 41:29.583
I know what you look like.

41:31.041 --> 41:32.875
Fucking take care
of your baby.

41:33.041 --> 41:34.041
[baby continues crying]

41:36.375 --> 41:37.500
[Stewart] Give us
the room a minute.

41:41.541 --> 41:43.041
-Cap.
-Ray.

41:43.833 --> 41:44.833
[Lou] Hmm.

41:48.958 --> 41:49.958
[door closes]

41:53.083 --> 41:54.708
So what's your objective?

41:55.041 --> 41:56.708
-What do you mean?
-[Stewart] You just turned

41:56.875 --> 41:58.375
a bunch of random robberies
into a series.

41:58.541 --> 42:00.208
You understand what that means
for the department, right?

42:00.958 --> 42:02.208
I understand
that we're gonna have to...

42:02.375 --> 42:03.291
Let me finish. Let me finish.

42:04.125 --> 42:05.708
Two of your little...

42:05.875 --> 42:09.208
examples there are cases
that already have suspects.

42:09.375 --> 42:10.708
Another one
was closed by Fellner

42:10.875 --> 42:12.000
six weeks ago, you understand?

42:12.166 --> 42:13.000
Uh...

42:13.166 --> 42:15.125
Yeah, but he was wrong.

42:15.291 --> 42:16.291
No.

42:16.916 --> 42:18.291
No, he wasn't wrong.

42:18.458 --> 42:20.041
He went from
red to black on the board.

42:20.208 --> 42:21.291
That's never wrong.

42:22.583 --> 42:24.083
You know what we don't do?

42:26.291 --> 42:28.958
We don't reverse
our fucking clearance rates.

42:29.125 --> 42:30.166
That's wrong.

42:30.333 --> 42:31.166
But I know I'm right,

42:31.250 --> 42:33.583
because all of these
are the same guy

42:33.750 --> 42:35.958
and he doesn't
let himself get caught.

42:36.125 --> 42:37.875
Right, right. [chuckles]

42:38.041 --> 42:40.250
Your one brilliant factor
tying these all together...

42:40.416 --> 42:41.541
your guy's untraceable.

42:41.708 --> 42:42.833
Oh, come on.
You and I both know

42:43.000 --> 42:43.958
there's nothing here
that's random.

42:44.125 --> 42:45.083
Stop talking.

42:46.291 --> 42:48.875
[chuckles] Okay.

42:49.041 --> 42:50.166
[Stewart] Okay.

42:50.333 --> 42:52.375
You got the lowest
clearance rate on the squad.

42:52.541 --> 42:54.958
It's pulling everyone down,
me included.

42:55.958 --> 42:56.958
What's the matter with you?

42:57.541 --> 42:58.708
You used to be the...

42:59.333 --> 43:01.750
You should've been sitting
in my seat by now, man.

43:02.583 --> 43:03.750
Play the game.

43:04.083 --> 43:05.333
Find a theory

43:05.500 --> 43:08.583
that works
for the whole building.

43:14.541 --> 43:16.916
[door opens, shuts]

43:37.166 --> 43:38.041
[phone chimes]

43:41.791 --> 43:43.750
-[phone chimes]
-[intriguing music playing]

43:58.833 --> 44:00.125
[phone dings]

44:01.625 --> 44:02.916
[phone clatters]

44:08.375 --> 44:09.500
[woman 1] And he
bought me flowers...

44:09.666 --> 44:11.583
[woman 2] Remind me again
what it is you do.

44:11.750 --> 44:15.166
[man 1] It's basically
software sales to banks.

44:15.333 --> 44:16.333
[man 2] Blanquette
de veau here

44:16.500 --> 44:17.583
apparently is superb.
I mean...

44:22.166 --> 44:23.291
[Maya clears throat]

44:24.375 --> 44:26.041
-[Maya] Hey, sorry I'm late.
-Hey. That's okay.

44:26.208 --> 44:28.375
I crashed into someone

44:28.541 --> 44:29.958
and those things
take a long time to sort out.

44:30.125 --> 44:30.958
[sighs]

44:31.125 --> 44:33.125
I'm guessing
he stopped too fast, huh?

44:34.333 --> 44:37.166
You know what? He did,
and it was fully his fault,

44:37.333 --> 44:39.458
but I got another
hot date out of it, so...

44:39.625 --> 44:40.625
[Davis chuckles]

44:41.458 --> 44:43.000
-[mumbles]
-[Maya clears throat]

44:45.416 --> 44:46.541
Do you come here a lot?

44:47.291 --> 44:49.125
Uh, couple times, yeah.
Couple of times.

44:50.166 --> 44:51.166
The, um...

44:52.000 --> 44:53.791
The blanquette de veau
is, it's good.

44:53.958 --> 44:54.833
Supposed to be good.

44:59.500 --> 45:00.791
Are you, um...

45:01.500 --> 45:02.791
Are you in LA?

45:03.666 --> 45:06.000
-Uh... I move around a lot.
-Do you?

45:06.166 --> 45:07.791
Yeah. For work.

45:08.458 --> 45:09.833
What is it you do?

45:10.000 --> 45:11.666
Basically, uh...

45:11.833 --> 45:13.583
software development...

45:14.000 --> 45:15.333
Um...

45:15.500 --> 45:16.916
for banks. It's sales.

45:17.083 --> 45:19.208
It's not very interesting...

45:19.375 --> 45:21.291
No, it's cool.

45:22.416 --> 45:23.416
[Davis] Yeah.

45:24.583 --> 45:26.416
[Maya clears throat] Mmm.

45:28.416 --> 45:29.416
You okay?

45:29.916 --> 45:32.333
[hesitantly] Yeah. Um...

45:33.708 --> 45:36.583
I think maybe
this wasn't a great idea.

45:37.000 --> 45:39.666
You seem super great
and you're very...

45:40.416 --> 45:43.166
Uh... [chuckles] But I, um...

45:43.333 --> 45:46.958
I honestly just don't see us
having all that much...

45:47.500 --> 45:48.666
in common.

45:48.833 --> 45:49.958
And I kind of have a rule

45:50.125 --> 45:51.500
where if it doesn't feel right

45:51.666 --> 45:53.583
you just don't waste
each other's time.

45:54.875 --> 45:56.125
What... But how do you know?

45:56.541 --> 45:57.708
How do I know what?

45:57.875 --> 45:59.666
That we won't have
anything in common.

46:00.208 --> 46:01.041
Uh...

46:01.750 --> 46:04.208
Well, I have no idea
what blanquette de veau is.

46:06.041 --> 46:07.291
I mean, I would just...

46:07.458 --> 46:09.708
I would never come
to a place like this.

46:09.875 --> 46:10.875
[Davis] Yeah...

46:11.833 --> 46:13.041
me neither.

46:14.333 --> 46:15.333
Really?

46:17.666 --> 46:18.791
I've never been here before.

46:18.958 --> 46:20.291
[chuckles] You've never
been here?

46:20.458 --> 46:22.541
Just thought it was the kind
of place that people...

46:22.708 --> 46:24.708
[clears throat]
...you know, take people.

46:25.791 --> 46:26.791
[Maya] Um...

46:28.125 --> 46:29.333
I think it's veal.

46:30.333 --> 46:31.333
What?

46:32.916 --> 46:33.750
Blanquette de veau.

46:33.833 --> 46:36.000
-Oh. Oh, veal. [chuckles]
-[Davis] Yeah.

46:36.833 --> 46:38.291
Yeah, I, um...

46:38.458 --> 46:40.458
No. I would not eat that.

46:40.625 --> 46:42.708
-Definitely not.
-What would you eat?

46:48.708 --> 46:49.666
[Lou sighs]

46:56.250 --> 46:58.083
I thought we loved each other.

46:59.958 --> 47:01.000
Yeah, we do.

47:01.166 --> 47:04.666
But more in a force of habit
kind of way, right?

47:07.208 --> 47:08.333
I mean, don't you want

47:08.500 --> 47:10.541
something you can
be excited about?

47:10.708 --> 47:12.625
-Something new?
-[cellphone buzzing]

47:13.750 --> 47:14.583
You can get it. Go.

47:14.750 --> 47:16.000
No, I'm fine. I don't need to.

47:17.208 --> 47:19.375
-[Angie] Pick it up.
-No, I'm not picking it up.

47:30.750 --> 47:32.166
Is it your first?

47:34.500 --> 47:35.750
Affair?

47:39.375 --> 47:40.916
Do you really wanna know?

47:45.666 --> 47:46.666
[scoffs]

47:49.375 --> 47:51.208
I'm gonna move out
at the weekend.

47:53.625 --> 47:56.125
No, you know what?
You stay. I'll move out.

47:57.041 --> 47:58.125
Where are you gonna go?

47:58.291 --> 48:00.125
Maybe I'll move to the beach.

48:00.291 --> 48:01.375
The beach?

48:01.541 --> 48:02.375
Are you serious?

48:02.458 --> 48:03.958
You're the least
beach person I know.

48:04.125 --> 48:05.583
I'm way more beach
than you are.

48:05.750 --> 48:06.916
[Angie] Bullshit.

48:08.583 --> 48:10.083
[Maya] "How did your
last relationship end?"

48:11.500 --> 48:13.666
Work. I had to move.

48:15.375 --> 48:16.791
"What motivates you?"

48:19.416 --> 48:20.625
Money, I guess.

48:21.166 --> 48:22.000
[Maya sighs]

48:22.333 --> 48:23.375
What?

48:24.208 --> 48:26.041
Okay, um...

48:28.541 --> 48:30.333
"Have you ever
used handcuffs?"

48:30.500 --> 48:31.500
Yeah.

48:36.916 --> 48:37.791
Okay.

48:37.958 --> 48:40.458
Uh, "If you had the option
to press a button..."

48:40.625 --> 48:43.083
Oh, "...and start your life
over, would you press it?"

48:43.541 --> 48:44.625
Yeah.

48:45.291 --> 48:46.208
You would?

48:46.375 --> 48:47.500
[Davis] Mmm-hmm.

48:47.666 --> 48:48.666
You?

48:49.791 --> 48:50.791
No.

48:51.833 --> 48:52.958
What's wrong?

48:53.125 --> 48:54.791
I don't know.
I mean, it's kinda...

48:56.625 --> 48:57.625
What?

48:58.666 --> 48:59.750
Sad?

49:01.666 --> 49:03.583
Okay, look,
I work for a publicist

49:03.750 --> 49:07.250
and we work with musicians
and actors and stuff

49:07.416 --> 49:08.833
and like...

49:09.000 --> 49:09.958
I swear to you,
it doesn't matter

49:10.041 --> 49:10.958
how much money they make

49:11.041 --> 49:12.041
it's never enough.

49:12.833 --> 49:14.458
I'll know when I have enough.

49:15.291 --> 49:16.625
How?

49:16.791 --> 49:18.791
I have a number in mind,
but, uh...

49:20.416 --> 49:22.416
I know it's just enough
to feel...

49:23.291 --> 49:24.541
well...

49:25.291 --> 49:26.458
safe.

49:32.333 --> 49:35.166
So you think
maybe, uh, you wanna...

49:37.958 --> 49:39.958
-Meet up again?
-Yeah.

49:42.500 --> 49:43.500
[Maya] Hmm.

49:48.166 --> 49:49.166
Maybe.

49:50.666 --> 49:52.083
Yeah?

49:53.750 --> 49:54.750
Yeah.

49:58.958 --> 50:01.208
[reporter] ...armed with
a semi-automatic weapon

50:01.375 --> 50:03.583
terrorized the staff
and customers

50:03.750 --> 50:05.375
in an extremely
violent assault

50:05.541 --> 50:07.375
in which shots were fired.

50:07.541 --> 50:09.000
It happened in Santa Barbara

50:09.166 --> 50:10.208
at a high-end jeweler

50:10.375 --> 50:12.041
in the Central
commercial district

50:12.208 --> 50:14.000
a little after 10 a.m.

50:14.166 --> 50:16.250
The intruder was captured
by surveillance cameras

50:16.583 --> 50:18.333
but is said to have worn
a motorcycle helmet

50:18.500 --> 50:20.083
throughout the robbery.

50:20.250 --> 50:23.000
This follows a string
of high-profile robberies

50:23.166 --> 50:24.916
in Southern California.

50:25.500 --> 50:26.875
[woman] I don't work here!
I don't work here!

50:26.958 --> 50:27.833
[Lou] Okay, pause it.

50:27.916 --> 50:29.500
[woman] No, no, no!

50:31.375 --> 50:33.500
Uh, can we interview
your witnesses?

50:34.500 --> 50:35.875
They're not gonna
be able to give you much.

50:36.041 --> 50:37.416
The guy was wearing
a motorcycle helmet

50:37.583 --> 50:38.708
the whole time.

50:40.125 --> 50:41.958
One of 'em shit their pants.

50:42.625 --> 50:43.791
Literally.

50:44.333 --> 50:46.333
Shit in his pants.

50:51.666 --> 50:53.291
Well, well, well.

50:54.458 --> 50:56.291
The 101 robber.

50:58.833 --> 51:00.333
There he is, Lou.

51:03.125 --> 51:04.000
[sniffles]

51:04.083 --> 51:05.750
Yeah,
something doesn't add up.

51:06.791 --> 51:08.791
-I'm sorry, what?
-Just...

51:08.958 --> 51:10.250
What do you mean, "Something
doesn't add up," Lou?

51:10.416 --> 51:11.416
You said
he was gonna hit north.

51:11.583 --> 51:12.500
Boom. He hits north, okay?

51:12.666 --> 51:14.583
We're barely a mile
from the 101,

51:14.750 --> 51:16.583
so the location fits,
the target fits,

51:16.666 --> 51:17.541
the M.O., it fits, Lou.

51:17.625 --> 51:18.458
So, which...

51:18.541 --> 51:19.375
I'm sorry, which bit
doesn't add up?

51:19.541 --> 51:20.791
Our guy never hurt anyone.

51:23.041 --> 51:24.416
[indistinct chatter]

51:28.958 --> 51:30.958
Ah, here's my champ.

51:31.125 --> 51:32.458
What you got going?

51:33.416 --> 51:35.458
Where's my account
for the last job?

51:35.625 --> 51:36.791
Why? What's the matter?

51:36.958 --> 51:39.333
Santa Barbara
was the last job.

51:39.875 --> 51:41.041
Oh.

51:41.125 --> 51:42.166
Santa Barbara.

51:42.333 --> 51:43.416
[Davis] Yeah, I found it.

51:43.583 --> 51:45.333
I planned it.
I walked you through it.

51:45.500 --> 51:47.666
And you said
you didn't wanna do it.

51:47.833 --> 51:49.208
It wasn't yours to give away.

51:49.958 --> 51:51.541
You want a cut, is that it?

51:51.708 --> 51:53.083
It's not about
the fucking money.

51:53.250 --> 51:54.875
Well, then what is it about?

51:58.541 --> 52:00.125
It's about trust.

52:04.833 --> 52:07.666
This happens again,
I think you and I are done.

52:08.625 --> 52:10.416
You and I are done?

52:12.875 --> 52:15.750
You're gonna threaten me now?

52:17.250 --> 52:19.041
Maybe you wanna have a think

52:19.208 --> 52:22.916
about where you'd be
without me, huh?

52:25.333 --> 52:26.500
Yeah.

52:27.375 --> 52:28.666
I'll be here

52:28.833 --> 52:29.916
when you come back

52:30.083 --> 52:32.833
with your tail
between your legs!

52:34.208 --> 52:36.500
[Sammy] Is this how you treat
all your customers

52:36.666 --> 52:39.291
or it's a special treatment
for immigrants?

52:39.458 --> 52:41.833
[Sharon] This is just
a formality, Mr. Kassem.

52:42.000 --> 52:43.291
If you have nothing to hide,

52:43.458 --> 52:45.833
then you've got absolutely
nothing to worry about.

52:46.000 --> 52:47.541
[Sammy] Oh, it's a formality.

52:48.416 --> 52:50.166
You know, what I object to

52:50.333 --> 52:52.500
is not that I pay you
to insure me

52:52.666 --> 52:53.833
and you look for ways

52:54.000 --> 52:55.666
to refuse
to give what you owe,

52:56.958 --> 52:58.875
it's that with this machine
you're saying

52:59.041 --> 53:00.833
not only,
"We think you're a thief"

53:01.000 --> 53:03.333
but also,
"We think you're a liar."

53:06.083 --> 53:09.458
You know, Ms. Coombs,
those people you work for,

53:09.625 --> 53:11.791
they're all parasites.

53:13.458 --> 53:16.458
Are you also a parasite?

53:20.083 --> 53:22.583
[intriguing music playing]

53:32.500 --> 53:33.375
[Ormon grunts]

53:34.083 --> 53:36.125
My guy, he's...

53:36.291 --> 53:38.375
planning something new.

53:39.083 --> 53:41.125
I need you to find him

53:41.291 --> 53:42.833
and I need you to follow him.

53:44.250 --> 53:47.500
Here's someone
he gets information from.

53:49.125 --> 53:51.291
He's a Google guy
or something.

53:51.458 --> 53:54.625
You watch him, he'll show up.

53:55.958 --> 53:57.333
Then what?

53:57.500 --> 53:59.833
You're not gonna rob
the courier.

54:00.000 --> 54:02.333
You let him do that...

54:03.666 --> 54:05.916
and then you'll rob him.

54:37.166 --> 54:38.041
[breathing heavily]

54:54.250 --> 54:56.750
[Davis sighs] "Step mom
butt sex dot com"?

54:57.541 --> 54:58.916
It's just
the encryption location.

54:59.083 --> 55:00.458
-Follow the steps.
-[Davis] Hmm.

55:01.541 --> 55:03.458
Yeah, it's funny what just

55:03.625 --> 55:05.166
floats to the top
of the old mind, huh?

55:09.916 --> 55:10.916
Thanks.

55:37.625 --> 55:38.583
[chuckles]

55:41.083 --> 55:42.083
[exhales sharply]

56:30.208 --> 56:31.166
[indistinct chatter]

56:39.333 --> 56:40.458
[Sharon] White Mercedes GLE,
please.

56:40.625 --> 56:42.541
Yes, ma'am. Coming right up.

56:45.625 --> 56:47.250
It's a cool car.

56:47.416 --> 56:48.500
[Sharon] Thanks.

56:49.041 --> 56:51.625
Life's too short
to drive boring cars, right?

56:53.375 --> 56:55.291
Elvis? He said that.

56:55.458 --> 56:57.541
Ah, right.
And what did he drive?

56:57.708 --> 56:59.625
See, that would be
a gold Cadillac.

56:59.791 --> 57:01.458
[both chuckle]

57:01.625 --> 57:02.875
Makes sense.

57:03.041 --> 57:04.750
You into cars?

57:04.916 --> 57:07.375
Ah, I like the ones
with a bit of character.

57:08.125 --> 57:10.291
Would that be old ones
or new ones?

57:10.875 --> 57:12.208
Today, an old one.

57:12.375 --> 57:13.375
[Sharon] Today?

57:14.833 --> 57:16.291
I need to be
in your line of work.

57:16.375 --> 57:17.250
[both chuckle]

57:17.916 --> 57:19.541
So what are we driving today?

57:19.708 --> 57:22.416
[sighs] If you can guess,
I'll give you the keys to it.

57:22.583 --> 57:23.583
Ooh.

57:24.125 --> 57:25.125
Be careful.

57:25.291 --> 57:26.291
I'm good at this.

57:26.458 --> 57:27.500
-Yeah?
-Mmm-hmm.

57:27.666 --> 57:28.666
All right.

57:28.833 --> 57:31.541
Okay. I'm gonna go with
a Chevy Chevelle.

57:32.166 --> 57:33.416
Color?

57:33.750 --> 57:35.000
Racing green.

57:36.250 --> 57:37.458
Right color.

57:39.333 --> 57:40.750
Well, one out of two,
that's not bad.

57:40.916 --> 57:42.041
[Davis] Not bad at all.

57:42.208 --> 57:44.333
[Sharon] That is
a beautiful car, though.

57:45.958 --> 57:47.458
I underestimated you.

57:47.625 --> 57:48.708
Mike.

57:48.875 --> 57:50.041
Sharon.

57:50.208 --> 57:51.375
Nice to meet you, Mike.

57:51.541 --> 57:52.916
[Davis] Nice to meet you, too.

57:59.583 --> 58:00.583
-[door closes]
-[engine starts]

58:04.125 --> 58:05.541
[key clacking]

58:06.875 --> 58:08.291
-[operator] Like I said...
-[Tillman] No...

58:08.458 --> 58:10.625
[operator] ...that's
the last image we have.

58:10.791 --> 58:12.875
[Lou] Are you certain
that we don't pick him up

58:13.041 --> 58:14.750
on the 101
in either direction?

58:14.916 --> 58:16.625
[operator sighs]
Still certain.

58:19.083 --> 58:21.833
Somewhere between that turn
and the 101, he switched cars.

58:22.000 --> 58:23.375
Why are you so convinced
he took the 101?

58:23.541 --> 58:24.541
Hey, don't ask, man.

58:24.708 --> 58:27.125
Look, there's 30 blocks
between there and the 101.

58:27.291 --> 58:28.541
-Let's get lookin'.
-Are you serious?

58:28.708 --> 58:30.416
-[Lou] I'm serious.
-Lou, come on, man.

58:30.583 --> 58:31.708
[Lou] How else
are we gonna find him?

58:32.375 --> 58:34.208
[Maya] The books
come with the place?

58:34.625 --> 58:36.083
-Uh-huh.
-[Maya] Huh.

58:38.750 --> 58:40.083
For someone
who likes things...

58:40.250 --> 58:41.875
you don't
really have a lot of...

58:43.041 --> 58:44.333
personal stuff.

58:46.750 --> 58:48.666
No photos of family or...

58:51.916 --> 58:53.208
Do you have any?

58:53.375 --> 58:54.458
What? Photos?

58:54.625 --> 58:56.583
[chuckles] No. Family.

58:57.500 --> 58:58.500
Yeah, someplace.

58:59.125 --> 59:00.250
Someplace?

59:00.416 --> 59:01.750
-What, like in a drawer?
-[Davis chuckles]

59:02.458 --> 59:04.250
I don't know, we're just
not really that kinda family.

59:04.416 --> 59:05.708
Don't really keep in touch.

59:05.875 --> 59:06.916
I don't know.

59:07.083 --> 59:09.416
Do you have,
like, brothers? Sisters?

59:09.583 --> 59:11.500
-Mom? Dad?
-[knife clangs]

59:12.875 --> 59:14.750
Yeah. Yeah.

59:14.916 --> 59:16.333
I don't know,
we didn't really, uh,

59:16.500 --> 59:17.666
have a lot of stuff growin' up

59:17.833 --> 59:19.333
and whatever we did have,

59:19.500 --> 59:20.791
I didn't really
keep any of it.

59:22.333 --> 59:23.333
So...

59:24.250 --> 59:26.250
[mellow music playing]

59:34.833 --> 59:35.833
What?

59:36.625 --> 59:37.916
Mystery man.

59:43.000 --> 59:44.083
Yeah.

59:44.791 --> 59:46.833
[Maya] Can I turn on
some music?

59:47.750 --> 59:48.875
[Davis] Yeah.

59:49.041 --> 59:51.458
There's a thing in the corner.

59:53.541 --> 59:54.625
Do you have a favorite song?

59:56.625 --> 59:58.166
Um...

59:58.333 --> 01:00:00.000
[Maya] No. Okay.

01:00:00.166 --> 01:00:01.416
I don't know why I would ask

01:00:01.583 --> 01:00:04.000
why you would have
a favorite song.

01:00:04.166 --> 01:00:06.125
[Davis] Suppose that's
another black mark, huh?

01:00:06.291 --> 01:00:07.291
[Maya chuckles]

01:00:08.083 --> 01:00:09.250
[Maya] Aye, yai, yai...

01:00:09.416 --> 01:00:11.041
-Do you, um...
-[device beeps]

01:00:11.208 --> 01:00:13.166
Do you listen to music or...

01:00:13.791 --> 01:00:14.875
Yeah, sometimes.

01:00:14.958 --> 01:00:15.833
[soft rock song playing]

01:00:15.916 --> 01:00:17.166
[Maya] Sometimes?

01:00:18.333 --> 01:00:19.500
You don't, do you?

01:00:24.750 --> 01:00:25.958
Come on.

01:00:27.625 --> 01:00:29.041
I can't dance.

01:00:36.291 --> 01:00:37.375
Come on.

01:00:38.458 --> 01:00:39.875
Come on.

01:00:42.541 --> 01:00:43.541
Come here.

01:00:43.708 --> 01:00:47.458
No photos,
no music, no dancing.

01:00:48.083 --> 01:00:51.166
Someone needs to teach you
how to be a human.

01:00:51.333 --> 01:00:52.333
Yeah.

01:00:55.541 --> 01:00:56.625
[Maya laughs]

01:00:59.333 --> 01:01:00.958
[crowd cheering
over music player]

01:01:01.125 --> 01:01:02.208
Ah.

01:01:03.125 --> 01:01:04.458
I love that.

01:01:05.625 --> 01:01:09.541
They cheer for home,
but no one does that for LA.

01:01:16.666 --> 01:01:18.000
[crowd cheering
over music player]

01:02:07.708 --> 01:02:08.708
[song fades]

01:02:09.916 --> 01:02:11.000
[Maya] Happy?

01:02:14.333 --> 01:02:15.333
Yeah.

01:02:19.666 --> 01:02:20.708
Yeah.

01:02:25.750 --> 01:02:26.750
Scared?

01:02:31.791 --> 01:02:32.875
Yeah, maybe.

01:02:35.458 --> 01:02:36.458
[exhales]

01:02:36.625 --> 01:02:38.625
[mellow music playing]

01:02:53.500 --> 01:02:54.708
You're not gonna stay?

01:03:08.333 --> 01:03:09.333
[exhales softly]

01:03:14.000 --> 01:03:15.416
[Maya] Do you want me to stay?

01:03:17.041 --> 01:03:18.041
[Davis] Yeah.

01:03:25.166 --> 01:03:26.250
Good.

01:03:34.750 --> 01:03:35.750
[door opens]

01:03:40.375 --> 01:03:41.208
[door closes]

01:04:00.333 --> 01:04:02.333
[tense music playing]

01:04:20.833 --> 01:04:22.208
[engine starts]

01:04:34.958 --> 01:04:36.000
[breathing heavily]

01:04:41.458 --> 01:04:42.500
[grunts]

01:04:42.666 --> 01:04:44.625
[panting]

01:04:45.166 --> 01:04:46.000
[Davis grunts]

01:04:57.083 --> 01:04:58.083
[line beeps]

01:04:58.250 --> 01:05:00.041
[Davis] Hi, this is Mr. Stone.

01:05:00.208 --> 01:05:01.166
I need a new apartment

01:05:01.333 --> 01:05:03.708
on the beach
available immediately.

01:05:06.000 --> 01:05:06.833
[door thuds]

01:05:22.375 --> 01:05:24.500
[doorbell buzzing]

01:05:29.750 --> 01:05:30.750
[Devon] Can I help you?

01:05:30.916 --> 01:05:31.916
[Ormon] Got delivery
for Wilson.

01:05:32.083 --> 01:05:33.708
I'm not expecting anything.

01:05:33.875 --> 01:05:35.041
[Ormon] It's got
your name on it.

01:05:35.208 --> 01:05:37.500
All right.
Just leave it outside.

01:05:37.666 --> 01:05:38.541
[Ormon] I'm not allowed
to do that.

01:05:38.708 --> 01:05:40.041
[sighs] All right.
Leave it in the hall.

01:05:40.208 --> 01:05:41.208
[door buzzes]

01:05:47.833 --> 01:05:48.958
-[door thuds]
-[Devon] Whoa!

01:05:49.125 --> 01:05:50.500
[Devon gasping]

01:05:50.666 --> 01:05:53.833
[Ormon] Move.
Come on, move. Move.

01:05:54.625 --> 01:05:56.583
[both grunting]

01:05:59.208 --> 01:06:00.083
Huh?

01:06:02.041 --> 01:06:04.458
You're gonna tell me what you
fucking gave him, okay?

01:06:05.708 --> 01:06:06.833
Fucking tell me.

01:06:06.916 --> 01:06:07.833
[panting]

01:06:09.750 --> 01:06:10.708
[Tillman] How many
more of these

01:06:10.875 --> 01:06:12.583
fucking garages you gonna
make us do tonight, man?

01:06:13.708 --> 01:06:15.000
[Tillman sighs]

01:06:15.166 --> 01:06:16.166
Hey, man...

01:06:19.333 --> 01:06:21.083
-Let's take a look.
-Have you...

01:06:21.250 --> 01:06:23.500
-See there?
-What? Now what?

01:06:34.458 --> 01:06:35.375
Lou.

01:06:35.541 --> 01:06:36.541
[car alarm beeping]

01:06:37.125 --> 01:06:37.958
[sighs deeply]

01:06:38.500 --> 01:06:40.333
Fuck's sake, man.

01:06:51.791 --> 01:06:53.041
[mumbles] Mmm. Huh.

01:06:58.666 --> 01:06:59.666
Call forensics.

01:06:59.833 --> 01:07:01.416
[man] Black
wasn't a color for him.

01:07:01.583 --> 01:07:03.250
It was his whole subject.

01:07:03.416 --> 01:07:04.458
[woman] I wouldn't
put it on my wall

01:07:04.625 --> 01:07:07.041
but I do love
the sense of drama.

01:07:07.208 --> 01:07:09.958
I think you can be confident
it's not gonna lose its value.

01:07:10.125 --> 01:07:11.708
The real question is...

01:07:11.875 --> 01:07:13.166
how much do you love it?

01:07:13.333 --> 01:07:14.541
Well, I love it.

01:07:14.708 --> 01:07:16.500
It'll go great
with the new chairs, you know.

01:07:16.666 --> 01:07:18.333
[Andrew] Really?
You sure you want this guy

01:07:18.500 --> 01:07:20.958
glaring down at us
every time we have dinner?

01:07:21.041 --> 01:07:21.958
[Beth] He's not glaring.

01:07:22.041 --> 01:07:23.041
[Andrew] He's glaring.

01:07:23.208 --> 01:07:25.166
[Beth] I'm sure.
And he isn't glaring, really.

01:07:25.333 --> 01:07:26.166
He's just looking, you know.

01:07:26.250 --> 01:07:27.208
Excuse me.
I'll be right with you.

01:07:27.291 --> 01:07:28.291
-[Beth] Okay.
-Sure. Thank you.

01:07:30.791 --> 01:07:32.625
Well, what a coincidence.

01:07:32.791 --> 01:07:33.791
[Davis] Hey.

01:07:33.958 --> 01:07:34.958
Uh, Sharon, right?

01:07:35.125 --> 01:07:36.125
-[Sharon] Yeah.
-Yeah.

01:07:36.291 --> 01:07:37.708
-Mike?
-That's it.

01:07:37.875 --> 01:07:39.166
-Yeah, good to see you.
-[Sharon] Hmm.

01:07:40.541 --> 01:07:41.375
Uh...

01:07:41.958 --> 01:07:44.458
So do you collect art
like you do cars, Mike?

01:07:44.625 --> 01:07:46.041
Uh, not really, but I like it.

01:07:47.083 --> 01:07:48.833
I like the sense of drama.

01:07:49.375 --> 01:07:51.416
[glass clinking]

01:07:52.041 --> 01:07:52.875
[Sharon] Hmm.

01:07:55.291 --> 01:07:57.125
Hey, do you maybe
wanna get out of here?

01:07:57.291 --> 01:07:59.125
Grab a drink or something?

01:08:00.000 --> 01:08:01.750
[Tillman] I swear, man...

01:08:01.916 --> 01:08:03.208
you divorced guys,
you always think

01:08:03.375 --> 01:08:04.208
you're gonna move to the beach

01:08:04.375 --> 01:08:06.166
and meet
some hot surfer chick.

01:08:06.333 --> 01:08:08.250
What you gonna do?
Take up surfing?

01:08:08.416 --> 01:08:11.166
No. I'm gonna...
Thinking of doing the yoga.

01:08:12.416 --> 01:08:13.625
The yoga?

01:08:15.166 --> 01:08:16.375
[Tillman laughs]

01:08:16.541 --> 01:08:18.707
'Course, you are. What kind?

01:08:19.375 --> 01:08:20.582
They got kinds?

01:08:20.750 --> 01:08:22.000
Big time, man.

01:08:22.166 --> 01:08:25.375
They got hot yoga, fast yoga,

01:08:25.541 --> 01:08:27.457
street yoga, Greek yoga.

01:08:27.625 --> 01:08:29.625
-Greek yoga?
-That last one might be food.

01:08:29.791 --> 01:08:31.207
[Tillman chuckling]

01:08:31.375 --> 01:08:33.082
So, you just wanna get laid.

01:08:33.250 --> 01:08:34.291
Oh, man, I wanna get fit.

01:08:34.457 --> 01:08:35.832
-Fitness?
-[sighs]

01:08:36.000 --> 01:08:38.000
-Please, booze man, you...
-[Lou] What's up?

01:08:38.166 --> 01:08:39.416
It's like a new car.

01:08:39.582 --> 01:08:40.957
Fuck.

01:08:41.125 --> 01:08:43.166
Except for one
microscopic speck of blood.

01:08:44.500 --> 01:08:46.207
[Tillman] Is it enough
to get DNA?

01:08:46.375 --> 01:08:47.625
[forensics officer] Should be.

01:08:47.791 --> 01:08:48.957
Let me see.

01:08:50.916 --> 01:08:52.832
[Davis] So, I guess
you work in the art world?

01:08:53.500 --> 01:08:55.166
[Sharon] Nope. Less glamorous.

01:08:55.332 --> 01:08:57.791
I write insurance policies
for people

01:08:57.957 --> 01:09:00.041
who have more money than
they know what to do with.

01:09:00.832 --> 01:09:01.707
[Davis] So, you must know

01:09:01.791 --> 01:09:03.000
a lot about
what things are worth, huh?

01:09:03.166 --> 01:09:05.375
Mmm-hmm. Too much.

01:09:05.541 --> 01:09:06.875
But I also have to know a lot

01:09:07.041 --> 01:09:08.916
about the people
that own these things.

01:09:09.000 --> 01:09:09.916
How do you mean?

01:09:10.000 --> 01:09:11.500
[Sharon] You know,
are you a thrill seeker,

01:09:12.082 --> 01:09:14.125
are you an alcoholic,
do you gamble,

01:09:14.291 --> 01:09:15.500
do you cheat on your partner?

01:09:15.666 --> 01:09:17.375
You know, all those questions
that you can't ask

01:09:17.541 --> 01:09:19.875
but you obviously need to know
the answers to.

01:09:20.707 --> 01:09:23.332
So, you get real good
at reading people.

01:09:23.791 --> 01:09:26.166
And what have you,
uh, read about me?

01:09:27.000 --> 01:09:28.250
[Sharon chuckles]

01:09:28.416 --> 01:09:29.416
Mmm-mmm.

01:09:30.250 --> 01:09:31.541
Things you don't like or what?

01:09:31.625 --> 01:09:32.541
[Sharon] Mmm-mmm.

01:09:32.625 --> 01:09:34.750
Nope. No, did not say that.

01:09:36.041 --> 01:09:36.875
[Sharon chuckles]

01:09:36.957 --> 01:09:38.125
Come on.

01:09:40.707 --> 01:09:41.707
Okay.

01:09:42.625 --> 01:09:45.916
[sighs] Well, you look like
a person who has secrets.

01:09:46.082 --> 01:09:47.541
-Is that right?
-[Sharon] Mmm-hmm.

01:09:47.707 --> 01:09:49.582
Your shirt's new
or newly pressed

01:09:49.750 --> 01:09:51.707
which says you don't
do your own laundry

01:09:51.875 --> 01:09:53.125
or you're a bit OCD.

01:09:53.291 --> 01:09:54.541
Uh, you're very groomed.

01:09:54.916 --> 01:09:56.416
Your hair, your nails,

01:09:56.583 --> 01:09:58.583
your 12-thousand-dollar
watch there,

01:09:59.250 --> 01:10:00.875
everything is just, uh...

01:10:02.000 --> 01:10:03.375
a little too perfect.

01:10:03.541 --> 01:10:05.041
Which tells me
you have a lot of money

01:10:05.208 --> 01:10:07.125
and a lot of time
on your hands, Mike.

01:10:07.958 --> 01:10:09.291
Got the clothes, the cars...

01:10:09.458 --> 01:10:11.583
but you can't seem
to look me in the eye.

01:10:11.750 --> 01:10:14.666
And I'd bet
you didn't grow up with money.

01:10:16.500 --> 01:10:17.500
How do you figure that?

01:10:17.833 --> 01:10:21.166
Because people who grow up
in chaos crave order.

01:10:24.041 --> 01:10:25.666
You talkin' about me or you?

01:10:27.083 --> 01:10:28.291
Maybe both.

01:10:31.208 --> 01:10:32.791
That hit too close to home?

01:10:34.791 --> 01:10:35.791
No.

01:10:38.708 --> 01:10:40.041
I have a...

01:10:40.708 --> 01:10:42.708
[clears throat]
I have a confession to make.

01:10:42.875 --> 01:10:43.875
[Sharon] Really?

01:10:44.541 --> 01:10:46.041
[laughs] I haven't even
finished my drink.

01:10:46.208 --> 01:10:49.541
This wasn't a coincidence.
Us meeting again.

01:10:51.750 --> 01:10:52.583
Oh.

01:10:53.291 --> 01:10:54.916
I came here to talk to you.

01:10:55.083 --> 01:10:56.083
You followed me?

01:10:56.250 --> 01:10:58.875
I came here to make you
a business proposition.

01:11:01.541 --> 01:11:04.708
You see, I know some things
about you, too, Sharon.

01:11:05.708 --> 01:11:07.500
Really? Like what?

01:11:07.666 --> 01:11:08.916
You live alone.
You're not married.

01:11:09.083 --> 01:11:10.541
You never have been.

01:11:10.708 --> 01:11:11.791
No children.

01:11:11.958 --> 01:11:13.583
You've worked at the same
company for 11 years.

01:11:13.750 --> 01:11:15.833
You're a VP when you
should be a partner.

01:11:16.000 --> 01:11:16.875
Uh-huh. Who the fuck are you?

01:11:17.041 --> 01:11:17.958
[Davis] Just give me
30 seconds.

01:11:18.041 --> 01:11:18.875
No. I...

01:11:18.958 --> 01:11:20.208
[Davis] What
I have to offer you

01:11:20.375 --> 01:11:22.041
is zero risk to you
and a huge upside,

01:11:22.208 --> 01:11:23.333
a life-changing upside.

01:11:23.500 --> 01:11:25.500
-No, that's okay. That's okay.
-[Davis] What I do...

01:11:25.666 --> 01:11:27.708
is I take certain pieces
of information

01:11:27.875 --> 01:11:29.083
from people like you

01:11:29.458 --> 01:11:31.791
and those
ultra high-value items

01:11:31.958 --> 01:11:33.541
belonging to the rich guys
you mentioned?

01:11:33.708 --> 01:11:35.625
Well, I occasionally
make them disappear.

01:11:36.083 --> 01:11:37.625
But I do it in a way
that no one can trace it,

01:11:37.708 --> 01:11:38.583
no one gets hurt...

01:11:38.666 --> 01:11:41.416
except maybe the shareholders
of companies like yours.

01:11:41.583 --> 01:11:42.583
Yeah.

01:11:43.708 --> 01:11:45.250
So, you're a thief?

01:11:46.125 --> 01:11:47.333
I get it.

01:11:48.375 --> 01:11:50.666
Let me tell you something,
Mike.

01:11:50.833 --> 01:11:53.166
I've gotten where I've gotten
through hard work.

01:11:53.333 --> 01:11:56.583
I don't lie. I don't steal,
and I certainly don't cheat.

01:11:56.750 --> 01:11:58.583
And I'm not
about to start now.

01:11:59.875 --> 01:12:02.041
